But it is plain enough that in prosecuting Plancius you rely on something more than these facts : you rely upon your general influence and name to crush Plancius, who has many personal enemies and detractors: and there are always plenty of men ready to give evidence in cases of ambitus. Cicero entreats the iudices to undertake the business of eroes-examining these witnesses and to relieve his own modesty from the unpleasant task, seeing they were his friends, and not to give any heed to idle reports about the defendant.
